Comment:
Excellent film that actually does a little more than it says it does on the side of the tin. What do I mean? Well its clever on a level that allows science to explain the real possibility that our "Moon" is nothing more than a "Mega Structure" but a twist to it. 

The world of academia has tried its best to hide a lot of stuff from us, for the sole purpose of trying to avoid mass panic... Which while its considerate, it begs the question is "Mankind" too dumb or stupid to really know the truth? Well it would suit a lot of people on our planet to not the truth, but for many of us who will always remain curious, it simply not acceptable.

At 63 years of age, I can happily throw away most of the text books on scientific stuff to say "Really". So let's take our planet first, as some say it's solid, and some say its hollow. This panicked scientists when we were testing Atomic bombs, because the Earth rang like a bell for hours. Just when we thought that was bad enough we literally ran a similar test on the "Moon" and you guessed right as that to rang like a bell.

In this movie, it discusses the idea, of the moon being a "Mega Structure" up to a point and then drifts away. What is subtle is that it does make a connection between the advance race that made the moon, and parked it in our orbit to keep an eye on us. Then we lose some interesting science which we were all led to believe was that the moon, was somehow responsible for the tides as it waxes and wanes. 

Slightly laughable and far from the truth, but we prefer to leave all of this down to the scientists. Theirs our biggest mistake. So what happened, well the time of the moon landing and events before that revealed to us that we were actually never alone. In fact it was even better than that. We weren't even first of any kind to have Earth as our home'.  Sometime ago, I had realized actually this planet isn't even known as Earth. 

What we do have is some very interesting neighbors who share our planet for the want of a better expression. They do, and they have done for a very, very long time. So long that it's mind boggling. This would be upsetting which is why disclosure has been so extremely difficult and delicate to manage. As we every civilization there are always drawbacks, and ours is no exception. 

The very complicated position we now have to deal with is explain that for the past 60-70 years we've done a few things that would actually mean that we were already space explorers and that we have already colonized other worlds... Yes, in one sense I can understand why it would freak people out, but in another sense its exciting that it's not beyond the realms of our abilities. 

The complications is whilst we work with our E.T. neighbors it has impacted upon things that are far, far , beyond what most of us could comprehend. So here's an example of a case that should have happened but didn't because our neighbors intervened.  Major Ed Dames was researching R.V. and by chance he was warning the People of Earth what was coming and it was pretty. However our neighbors did have the technology to prevent this event from happening, but it then raises the question, was it ethically right and who were they to decide the fate of the world and mankind as we know it. 

It's a galactic size problem, and the Galactic Federation clearly reached a decision for that intervention to be made. Which begs the next question was their an ulterior motive for doing so, later on which would benefit them having helped us?

Comment: There is so much wrong with this movie. The acting is good. But oh man this was bad. The premise is ok. If the moon fell towards earth there would be havoc. The havoc would just be worse. I can forgive them not wiping life on earth out. I also had no qualms with the whole ancient aliens bit & the moon being a dyson sphere. What I cant forgive is the lazy writing & lack of logic. How did they reject common sense & basic science throughout this movie? How did they have a space mission at the start with no ground control communicating with them? How was NASA run by stupid people? How does Elon Musk & Space X exist in your movie & yet they dont assist in the biggest space event in history? How did a random guys over complicated scifi gobbldygook trend on social media let alone become global news? How was America the only country aware of what was really going on? How was the biggest secret in the world being "guarded" by a random old dude in a wheelchair at a glorified storage unit instead of Area 51 or Cheyenne Mountain or Iron Mountain inc? How did they get a relic at a museum to fly to space? How do they have signal when every satellite would have been knocked out? How did they find Harper in a random motel? How did they survive launching through water & a gravitational anomaly? How did they fly blind through a debris field & not get destroyed? How did the guy who had a gun & was in a bulletproof humvee get hijacked by druggies? How did a whole general with a military at his command not send the army to get his kid? How did the gravitational pull of the moon lift buildings & cars but not people hiding in a wooden barn? How did the moon not deploy the fighter jets at its disposal & use its advanced weapons system to fight the AI virus? How did the moon rake through our atmosphere & not destroy it or cause global earthquakes & storms? How did the shuttle fly out of the moon at breakneck speed as the moon passed inside 30000ft & somehow land successfully with a parachute?How was this movie paced so fast that it made Game Of Thrones time jumps seem like reasonable timeframes? How did anyone allow Roland Emmerich to make this? How can anyone with even half a brain think this movie is good?

Comment:
This is, without hyperbole, the biggest pile of shit in history. The largest Blue whale would excrete less fecal matter. It's a film written by children for children and I already know it has regressed mankind, possibly causing untold sorrow for years to come. 

Anything that makes battlefield earth look like a well researched, plausible film deserves some credit, purely for the audacity of the producers and the sheer miracle that they managed to find funding (I presume an amoral cult didn't fund this one). 

While the special effects are very impressive, one has to wonder why some of the budget that must have gone into that couldn't have been reallocated to a scriptwriter who has at least left primary school. One wonders whether the dialogue being so poor that my ears are literally bleeding, was actually a clever decision to eventually drown itself out and thus save the cost of scientific advisors.

I am presuming, without checking, that the writer also directed this film, if not then they are evidently in a relationship of some sort. I say this because it is quite clear that the inevitable cries from the poor actors, as gallons of shite spewed from their mouths, were completely ignored.

Having said that, once the aneurysm subsided, I at least enjoyed the adrenaline pumping through my veins. Not from excitement or tension of course, this film has neither, but from the pure hatred for everyone involved in the production of this film.

I should say that the reason this film is bereft of tension is because the plot obviously includes the annihilation of Earth; after watching 15 minutes of this film I found myself praying for this to happen in reality just to ensure that those involved in the writing, production and directing of this film are prevented from creating anything else.
